title: Quint_2-67_Col-0-1h_Rep1_ATH1
description: ['After sterilization, seeds were incubated in sterile water in the dark for 5 days at 4Â°C prior to cultivation  Seed were washed briefly (4 min) in 70% ethanol followed by an 8 min treatment with bleach. Afterwards seeds were washed 3 times with sterile deionised water. After final wash, seeds were resuspended in sterile deionised water and subjected to stratification  Sterilized and stratified seeds were grown in 300 ml Erlenmeyer flasks containing 100 ml of sterile liquid ATS medium. Plants were cultivated on a shaker for 7 days at 90 rpm and 22 Â°C under constant white fluorescent light. For the last 24 hours of cultivation the light was filtered by yellow plexiglas (yellow 2208)to prevent photodegradation of IAA.  Reference for ATS medium:', 'Lincoln C, Britton JH, Estelle M (1990) Growth and Development of the axr1 Mutants of Arabidopsis. Plant Cell 2: 1071-1080  autoclaved  22 Â°C average, 22 Â°C day, 22 Â°C night 70 % average, 70 % day, 70 % night Own medium: ATS medium according to Lincoln et al. (1990)  Constant light']
characteristics_ch1: ['strain/ecotype: Col-0 (Columbia)', 'developmental stage: 1.0', 'tissue: whole plant', 'stock code: N1092']

title: Robertson_1-1_WT-untreated-49hr_Rep1_ATH1
description: The seeds were stratified at 4C for 48 hours in darkness.  Seeds were rinsed in 100% ethanol and sterilized in 2.5% (v/v) sodium hypochlorite solution for 7 min, then washed with sterilized distilled water 3 times.  70-100 Seeds were plated in 10 clusters (app 10 seeds per cluster) on 1/2 MS 0.8% agar plates.  Seedlings were grown in 12 h light/12 h dark (12L:12D) for 11 days at constant 19C. The light source for germination and growth was cool-white fluorescent light at 70 umol/m2/s. On the 12th day the seedlings were transferred to continuous white light conditions at 100 umol/m2/s.  10-20 seeds clumped together. 19 C average, 19 C day, 19 C night. 50 % average, 50 % day, 50 % night. Murashige & Skoog basal salt mixture. 12 hour days, 12 hour nights.
characteristics_ch1: ['developmental stage: 1.03', 'tissue: aerial tissue', 'genotype: wild type', 'treatment: none', 'time: 49hr']

Seeds were rinsed in 100% ethanol and sterilized in 2.5% (v/v) sodium hypochlorite solution for 7 min, then washed with sterilized distilled water 3 times.  70-100 Seeds were plated in 10 clusters (app 10 seeds per cluster) on 1/2 MS 0.8% agar plates. Seedlings were grown in 12 h light/12 h dark (12L:12D) for 11 days at constant 19C. The light source for germination and growth was cool-white fluorescent light at 70 umol/m2/s. On the 12th day the seedlings were transferred to continuous white light conditions at 100 umol/m2/s.  10-20 seeds clumped together. 19 C average, 19 C day, 19 C night. 50 % average, 50 % day, 50 % night. Murashige & Skoog basal salt mixture. 12 hour days, 12 hour nights.
characteristics_ch1: ['developmental stage: 1.04', 'tissue: aerial tissue', 'genotype: wild type', 'treatment: nicotinamide', 'time: 69hr']

title: Quint_2-5_Bay-0-30min_Rep2_ATH1
description: ['After sterilization, seeds were incubated in sterile water in the dark for 5 days at 4Â°C prior to cultivation  Seed were washed briefly (4 min) in 70% ethanol followed by an 8 min treatment with bleach. Afterwards seeds were washed 3 times with sterile deionised water. After final wash, seeds were resuspended in sterile deionised water and subjected to stratification  Sterilized and stratified seeds were grown in 300 ml Erlenmeyer flasks containing 100 ml of sterile liquid ATS medium. Plants were cultivated on a shaker for 7 days at 90 rpm and 22 Â°C under constant white fluorescent light. For the last 24 hours of cultivation the light was filtered by yellow plexiglas (yellow 2208)to prevent photodegradation of IAA.  Reference for ATS medium:', 'Lincoln C, Britton JH, Estelle M (1990) Growth and Development of the axr1 Mutants of Arabidopsis.
